
[1]apode

   AP'ODE, n. [Gr. foot.]

   An animal that has no feet, applied to certain fabulous fowls, which
   are said to have no legs, and also to some birds that have very short
   legs.

   In zoology, the apodes are an order of fishes which have no ventral
   fins; the first order in Linne's system.
